          "name": "API Support",
          "url": "https://news-public-api.onrender.com/"
        },
        "description": "This API provides access to the latest news articles, allowing users to fetch and retrieve news data programmatically. It is built using Python REST Framework and is available for public use.",
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Production server",
            "url": "https://news-public-api.onrender.com"
          }
        ],
        "title": "News Public API",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Fetch latest news articles as JSON from a Django REST Framework backend",
        "homepage": "https://news-public-api.onrender.com",
        "docs_url": "https://freepublicapis.com/news-public-api",
        "about_md": "News Public API is a small, free public endpoint that serves news articles as JSON. It is built on Python with Django REST Framework and hosted on Render, with a community catalogue page on [Free Public APIs](https://freepublicapis.com/news-public-api).\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n\n- A list of recent news items via `GET /api/noticias/`\n- Bulk fetch with `?all=true` to retrieve all available articles\n- Pagination-style limiting with `?limit=<n>` (for example, `?limit=50`)\n\nOperational notes: the service has been observed to be intermittent on its free Render hosting and CORS is not enabled, so direct browser-side calls from another origin may be blocked. No authentication is documented.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "noticia": "A news article resource exposed at `GET /api/noticias/`, supporting `?all=true` and `?limit=<n>` query parameters."
        },
